{{Infobox power station | name = Hardeland Hydroelectric Power Station | name_official = ''Hardeland kraftverk'' | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Norway | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | location_map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|59|39|27|N|6|05|48|E|region:NO-12_type:landmark_source:kolossus-nowiki|display=inline,title}} | country = Norway | location = | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = Haugaland Kraft | operator = | psps_upper_res = | psps_upper_res_capacity= | psps_penstocks = | psps_lower_res = | psps_lower_res_capacity= | psps_hydraulic_head = | psps_generators = 3 × 14&nbsp;MW | psps_pumpgenerators = | psps_pumps = | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_manu_model = [[Pelton wheel]] | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_electrical_capacity = 42 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = 33.4%<!-- 123,000 MWh/year / ( 42 MW * 365 days/year * 24h/day) = 0.334 --> | ps_annual_generation = 123 | ps_annual_gen_year = | website = | extra = }} '''Hardeland hydroelectric power station''' is a power plant in [[Etne]] in western [[Norway]]. The site is owned and operated by [[Haugaland Kraft]].
The station uses water from two sets of [[reservoir]]s. Hardeland H is a 400&nbsp;m vertical fall from [[Løkjelsvatnet]], while Hardeland K uses Grindheimsvatnet, Ilsvatnet, Basurde-/Krokavatnet and Hjørnås via a 305&nbsp;m fall from the Hjørnås lake.
Hardeland is connected to the grid with a 22&nbsp;[[kilovolt|kV]] line to [[Litledalen]].<ref>http://www.josok-prosjekt.no/List%20of%20reference%202006.pdf</ref> The site uses three [[pelton wheel]]s with 14&nbsp;MW generators, and average yearly output is 123&nbsp;GWh.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.haugaland-kraft.no/category.php?categoryID=124 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-01-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071009003732/http://www.haugaland-kraft.no/category.php?categoryID=124 |archivedate=2007-10-09 |df= }}</ref>
